# Manual API smoke tests — open in REST Client (VS Code) or run via curl.
# All quiz endpoints require an LNURL-auth session cookie (`quiz_session`).

### LNURL-auth: bootstrap a challenge (returns k1 + bech32 LNURL)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/lnurl/init

### Headless LNURL-auth signing — paste the k1 from /init above:
###   cd quiz/app && node -e '
###     const s = require("@noble/secp256k1"); const c = require("crypto");
###     s.utils.hmacSha256Sync = (k, ...m) => {
###       const h = c.createHmac("sha256", Buffer.from(k));
###       m.forEach(b => h.update(Buffer.from(b))); return h.digest();
###     };
###     const k1 = process.argv[1];
###     const priv = s.utils.randomPrivateKey();
###     const pub = s.getPublicKey(priv, true);
###     const sig = s.signSync(Buffer.from(k1, "hex"), priv);
###     console.log("sig=" + Buffer.from(sig).toString("hex"));
###     console.log("key=" + Buffer.from(pub).toString("hex"));
###   ' <K1_HEX>
###
### Then hit the callback the wallet would hit:
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/lnurl/callback?tag=login&k1={{k1}}&sig={{sig}}&key={{key}}

### LNURL-auth: poll until authenticated; on success sets `quiz_session` cookie
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/lnurl/status?k1={{k1}}

### LNURL-auth: who am I
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/me

### LNURL-auth: log out
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/logout

### Wallet provisioning (anonymous — for users without a Plan B Signet wallet)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/wallet/create

### Start today's quiz (5 personalised questions, requires session)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/start
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### Submit answers (5/5 mints an LNURL-withdraw, requires session)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/submit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "score": 5,
  "total": 5
}

### LNURL-withdraw: phase 1 — wallet asks for service params (returns withdrawRequest)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/withdraw/lnurl?k1={{withdraw_k1}}

### LNURL-withdraw: phase 2 — wallet pushes its bolt11 (server pays from Big Pot)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/withdraw/lnurl?k1={{withdraw_k1}}&pr={{bolt11}}

### LNURL-withdraw: poll claim status (requires session)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/withdraw/status?k1={{withdraw_k1}}

### LNURL-withdraw: most recent unclaimed withdraw for the current session
GET http://localhost:3000/api/withdraw/active

### Attempts log
GET http://localhost:3000/api/logs
